cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.IT. 

The paper focuses on resource allocation for mobile-edge cloud computing, which involves both networking and computation aspects. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a computation offloading mechanism and a joint communication and computation resource allocation mechanism, which are related to distributed computing and data structures, respectively. Hence, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely categories. The paper also deals with admission control and pricing, which are related to system design and information theory, respectively. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also possible categories.
